==English==

===Verb===
'''[[hold]] [[on]]'''

# To [[grasp]] or [[grip]] firmly.
#: '''''Hold on''' tight to the railing.''
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} To [[keep]]; to [[store]] something for someone.
#: '''''Hold on''' to my umbrella while I ride the roller coaster.''
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} [[wait|Wait]] a short [[while]].
#: '''''Hold on''' while I get my coat.''
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} To remain [[loyal]].
#: ''He didn't give up his fandom when others did; he '''held on'''''.
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} To [[persist]]
